sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Git
    participant Sshenc as sshenc -Y sign
    participant Agent as sshenc-agent
    participant Backend as sshenc-se
    participant LibEA as libenclaveapp
    participant Host as GitHub / verifier

    User->>Git: git commit
    Git->>Git: gpg.format=ssh and commit.gpgsign=true
    Git->>Git: Read user.signingkey public key path
    Git->>Sshenc: Invoke gpg.ssh.program as ssh-keygen -Y sign compatible command
    Sshenc->>Sshenc: Intercept -Y sign before normal CLI parsing
    Sshenc->>Sshenc: Read public key and build SSHSIG pre-sign bytes
    Sshenc->>Agent: Ensure agent is ready and send SignRequest
    Agent->>Backend: Match public key blob to stored identity
    Backend->>LibEA: Sign SSHSIG pre-sign bytes
    LibEA-->>Backend: DER ECDSA signature from platform backend
    Backend-->>Agent: SSH-format signature
    Agent-->>Sshenc: SignResponse
    Sshenc-->>Git: PEM-armored SSHSIG v1 signature
    Git-->>User: Commit object with SSH signature
    User->>Host: Push commit and public signing key
    Host-->>User: Signature shown as verified when key is trusted
